\end{aligned}
$$
Next, we take the derivative of $a_J$ with respect to $J$ and set the derivative equal to zero to find the maximum of the function:
$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{d a_J}{d J} & =0=\frac{d}{d J} N \beta h c B(2 J+1) e^{-\beta h c B J(J+1)} \\
