2 & =\beta h c B(2 J+1)^2=\frac{h c B}{k T}(2 J+1)^2 \\
T & =\frac{(2 J+1)^2 h c B}{2 k}
\end{aligned}
$$
Substitution of $J=4$ into the preceding expression results in the following temperature at which the spectrum was obtained:
$$
